  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-heading reveal">
      <span class="idx">05</span>
      <h2>About</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="prose reveal">
      <p>
        I lead operations for a living. Today I run a multi-million-dollar
        distribution center as a General Manager; before that I spent 12 years at
        Union Pacific Railroad, working up from train dispatcher to corridor and
        yard-operations manager — coordinating crews, traffic, and safety across
        thousands of miles.
      </p>
      <p>
        Somewhere along the way I got tired of waiting on reports and started
        building my own — Power BI dashboards, Excel tooling, then automations
        and AI agents that turn operational data into decisions. What began as
        scratching my own itch became a second skill set: self-hosted
        multi-agent systems, eval-gated trading automation, and a growth engine
        that put a 30-year-old foundry into Google's AI Overview and produced
        real inbound revenue.
      </p>
      <p>
        I lead people and I build systems. I care about outcomes over demos,
        culture as much as numbers, and turning "what if" into "running in
        production." If that mix is useful to your team, let's talk.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

